   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The fourth year of the new era: November</h2>

<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 1st, Tareyja Goldbach looks for a smith. However, she insists on the smith being human, which runs into negative reactions among the populace. This leads to an argument between Damien and Gandela, who both each claim to be better than the other.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 7th, Jeremy Gems Willowbrook reminds people to respect the new rules of forestry again. He refers specifically to the regulation set up by Caitlin Fergus, which forbids to enter the eastern forest.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 8th, Aristeaus leaves the island for "some time", as it is said.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 12th, Lennier invites to a celebration in the Castle of the Grey Rose, which is to be held in the following week. The reason behind the festival is the knighting of Gorden Fisk.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 13th, Cliu Beothach offers to serve as a teacher for the finer arts of playing the harp and the lute. The price is 25 gold pieces per hour.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 13th, Edwina gives birth to her daughter Feliana.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 14th, Dhalsim retires from his duty as leader of the Druids of the Forest, and declares Caitlin Fergus to be his successor, because he is going to leave the island. Some members leave the circle because they disapprove with the fashion of the change of leaders.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 16th, the Zelphia Temple is subject to gossip because of a priest having supposedly stolen. He, however, explained that he relieved the supposed victim from his magic wand because he had been abusing his magic in town.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 16th, the citizen scroll and the legislation of Varshikar are newly published.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 16th, in the morning, Randelon Morgental is found dead inside his chamber within the Eldan Monastery.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 16th, four of the island's populace fall from a cliff to their deaths.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 16th, Talaena Landessi announces her resignation from the Concubius guild. She also renounces her right to enter Varshikar. She departs from the island in direction of her homelands.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 16th, the dwarf Rackere Diplomatre reports a mysterious discovery of gold in a coal mine, which is not confirmed, but results in a short and adventurous trek to Varshikar.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 16th, Gorden Fisk is knighted by the Grey Rose. Shortly before the celebration, King Tialdin of Silverbrand returns to the island and participates in the festivities. A social gathering ensues that eve.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 16th, Aryllis reports a case of thievery. There is however no trial because the incident took place in Varshikar.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 17th, a message is to be read everywhere upon the island, which deals with the takeover of Varshikar by the Shenosss Clan. It was written by Moskher Heszche, a member of the Concubius.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 17th, a stranger named Nikargor announces his attempt to murder a woman who is a professional medico.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 18th, the member of the Triumvirate, Caitlin Fergus, is murdered.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 19th, Marius Eisenhauer announces that three suspects were arrested, who apparently were involved with the death of Caitlin Fergus. Aristeaus promises a reward for those who can locate the murderers of Caitlin Fergus.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 21st, Lennier releases information about the murderers of Caitlin Fergus. Several suspects are wanted, and a bounty is placed for capturing them.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 21st, Balcmeg reports the murder of Talaena Landessi by the lizard Sherg.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 21st, the dwarf Dolgan Durgan discovers gold in the coal mine.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 21st, Ules Felko seeks someone who could school him in the arts of magic. It entails a discussion about magic.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 22nd, a quarrel takes place between the ambassador of Varshikar in Troll's Bane and the dwarf Dolgan Durgan. At that, a physical argument comes to pass, resulting in Dolgan being banned from Troll's Bane for a week, and banned from Varshikar for an undetermined amount of time.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 24th, Lofosh Ironbreaker seeks someone who could heal his difficulties to breathe.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 24th, Gwynnether von Glanwen puts up a threat to hunt the orc who slew Galina and who was partly to blame for the death of Caitlin Fergus.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 24th, Nedor von Largon looks for all true friends of Caitlin Fergus and asks them to attend to a meeting.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 25th, Lysu Davanum looks for a priest of Tanora, Findari, Eldan, and Ushara each.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 26th, an unknown person pins a message to the wall of the library, upon which it is written that he has gone blind and requires aid.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 27th, Mardras asks the foresters of the city to replenish the amount of cherry trees and demands prohibition to cut them down.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 27th, hostilities between Troll's Bane and the Bloodskulls begin, due to an incident where several knights and orcs were involved.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 28th, the madman Ceigan Zain Ibatha founds a cult that worships the "Magenta Troll of Madness".</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 28th, a (strange) message by Dirt appears on the blackboard. It is written thereupon that the skeletons ask the Bloodskulls for a meeting, to clarify the armaments.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 28th, Lennier announces in the name of the Triumvirate that Elminister ben Gorion is the first judge of Troll's Bane from now on.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 30th, the Clan of the Axe initiates the hunt of the horde.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on November the 30th, Gannon looks for the owner of the building located south of the pig pen. He is informed that this land belongs to the Farmers Union.</p>

